To enable query builder logging in TypeORM, you can use the `logging` option in the `TypeOrmModule` configuration.

Here's an example of how to enable query builder logging:

```typescript
import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';
import { TypeOrmModule } from '@nestjs/typeorm';
import { AppController } from './app.controller';
import { AppService } from './app.service';
import { User } from './entities/user.entity';

@Module({
  imports: [
    TypeOrmModule.forRoot({
      type: 'sqlite',
      database: 'db.sqlite',
      entities: [User],
      logging: 'all', // or 'query' or 'error' to enable logging
      synchronize: true,
    }),
  ],
  controllers: [AppController],
  providers: [AppService],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

In the above example, the `logging` option is set to `'all'`, which will log all database queries, including those generated by the query builder.

You can also use `query` or `error` to enable logging, but they will only log specific types of queries.

```typescript
logging: 'query' // will log only queries
logging: 'error' // will log only errors
```

